insights: The Renault Tribut has been updated 6 years after its initial launch, with a focus on refreshing the exterior and interior design.
The updated Tribut features a new Renault badge, gloss black grille, and LED headlamps, giving it a more SUV-like appearance.
The car's wheelbase is substantial at 2636 mm, and it has a ground clearance of 182 mm, but it drives on 15-inch steel wheels with plastic wheel caps.
The Tribut has a boot space of 84 liters with all seats up, but this can be expanded to 625 liters by folding or removing the seats.
The interior has been redesigned with a new 8-inch screen, wireless Apple CarPlay, and Android Auto, as well as a digital instrument cluster and new materials such as matte wood and diamond patterns.
The updated Tribut features new safety and convenience features, including wireless Apple CarPlay, Android Auto, auto headlamps, and rain sensing wipers.
